{"word":"G2436 - ἵλεως - híleōs - hil'-eh-oce - Be it far","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἵλεως</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>híleōs"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>hil'-eh-oce"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Be it far"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"கிருபையாயுள்ள - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"propitious, merciful"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Perhaps from the alternate form of <a href=\"#/G138 - αἱρέομαι - hairéomai - hahee-reh'-om-ahee/138\">G138</a>; <i>cheerful</i> (as <i>attractive</i>), that is, <i>propitious</i>; adverbially (by Hebraism) God be <i>gracious!</i>, that is, (in averting some calamity) <i>far</i> be it: - be it far, merciful."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2433 - ἱλάσκομαι - hiláskomai - hil-as'-kom-ahee/2433\">G2433</a>, <a href=\"#/G2434 - ἱλασμός - hilasmós - hil-as-mos'/2434\">G2434</a>, <a href=\"#/G2435 - ἱλαστήριον - hilastḗrion - hil-as-tay'-ree-on/2435\">G2435</a>, <a href=\"#/G2436 - ἵλεως - híleōs - hil'-eh-oce/2436\">G2436</a>"}]}